OL,3,CMother remembers entering hospital and
OL,4,Crealising her son would never walk
OL,5,Cagain
OL,7,F"And them tickling the bottom of his
OL,8,Ffeet to see if there was any reaction
OL,9,Fand nothing happened.
OL,11,F"And I knew then that he'd probably
OL,12,Fnever walk again - and he can't."
OL,14,FSeth had got into a friend's car after
OL,15,Fthey had been out together drinking.
OL,16,FHe did not put on his seatbelt.
OL,18,FThe crash happened two years ago, but
OL,19,FSeth only came home in March this
OL,20,Fyear. He's just had more surgery.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
