OL,3,CMother remembers entering hospital and
OL,4,Crealising her son would never walk
OL,5,Cagain
OL,7,FSeth plans to go and talk to young
OL,8,Fpeople about his experience to try to
OL,9,Fmake them think of the consequences of
OL,10,Fmaking the wrong decisions.
OL,12,FHe is still affected by his injuries
OL,13,Ftoday and routinely has to visit the
OL,14,Fhospital.
OL,16,FJulie has spoken out as part of
OL,17,FNational Road Victim Month. Last year
OL,18,Falone, more than 700 people were
OL,19,Fkilled or seriously injured on the
OL,20,Froads of Devon and Cornwall.
